cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY

This paper involves the joint learning of numerical time series and textual corpora, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel multi-modal neural model, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The task of discovering relevant news articles for a given time series involves information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR another possible category. The use of neural networks for automated information filtering also falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with financial data, which involves cybersecurity (cs.CY) concerns, making it a less likely but still possible category.
